Student Performance Prediction using Machine Learning
Project Overview

This project is a Machine Learning web application that predicts a student's final exam score based on their academic habits such as study hours, attendance, sleep hours, and previous scores. It helps in understanding how student behavior affects academic performance.

Features
Predicts student final score using ML model
Simple and interactive Streamlit web app
Uses real dataset in CSV format
Fast and accurate predictions
Easy to use interface

Machine Learning Model

Algorithm: Linear Regression
Type: Supervised Learning (Regression)
Target: Final Score prediction

Input Features
Study Hours
Attendance
Sleep Hours
Previous Score

Output
Predicted Final Exam Score (0–100)

Technologies Used
Python 
Pandas
NumPy
Scikit-learn
Streamlit

